    "asOf": "2023-02-24",
    "date": "2023-07-11T19:29:42Z",
    "text": "Accountability for Government Censorship Act\n\nThis bill requires federal agencies to report any actions taken to suppress lawful speech on privately owned or operated platforms, including interactive computer services (e.g., social media).\n\nAgencies must report actions taken within the last five years to (1) remove or suppress lawful speech, (2) add disclaimers, information, or other alerts to lawful speech; or (3) remove or restrict access to a platform. Agencies must include specified details about these actions, including the names of the employees involved and the legal authority for taking the action."
  },
